g.text: JPA Main Classes, Interfaces and Annotations
An entity represents a table in a relational database.
The EntityManager API is used to create, read, update and delete operations for entities.
@Id is used to specify the primary key of an entity.
@GeneratedValue is used to specify the primary key generation strategy.
@Column is used to specify the mapped column for a persistent property or field.
@OneToMany is used to specify a one-to-many relationship between entities.
@ManyToOne is used to specify a many-to-one relationship between entities.
@Transient is used to specify that a field is not to be persisted in the database.
@Table is used to specify the primary table for an entity.
